# Constants Organization

**ALWAYS place constants in `app/lib/constants/`** to keep configurable values centralized and easy to maintain.

## File Structure

```
app/lib/constants/
  index.ts        # Re-exports all constants
  pricing.ts      # Pricing-related constants
  limits.ts       # Rate limits, size limits, etc.
  messages.ts     # User-facing messages, error text
  config.ts       # App configuration values
```

## When to Use Constants Files

Create constants in `app/lib/constants/` when:
- Values are used in multiple places
- Values might need to be changed/configured later
- Values represent business logic (pricing, limits, timeouts)
- Values are user-facing messages or labels

## Examples

```typescript
// ❌ BAD - hardcoded values scattered in code
const MAX_FILE_SIZE = 10 * 1024 * 1024;
const TIMEOUT_MS = 30000;

// ✅ GOOD - import from constants
import { MAX_FILE_SIZE, TIMEOUT_MS } from "@/lib/constants";
```

```typescript
// app/lib/constants/limits.ts
export const MAX_FILE_SIZE = 10 * 1024 * 1024; // 10MB
export const MAX_UPLOAD_COUNT = 5;
export const REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS = 30000;
```

```typescript
// app/lib/constants/index.ts
export * from "./limits";
export * from "./pricing";
export * from "./messages";
```

## Import Pattern

Always use the `@/lib/constants` alias:

```typescript
import { PRICE_AMOUNT, MAX_RETRIES } from "@/lib/constants";
```
